Indeed, using both sets of Eqs.(\ref{can_U}-\ref{can_mu}) or Eqs.(\ref{grand_U}-\ref{grand_N}) we obtain equivalent expressions (identifying $\langle N\rangle$ and $N$ and taking $N\to\infty$):
\begin{eqnarray}
U &=& -N \left(\frac{\partial \log {\cal Z}_1}{\partial \beta}\right)_{V},\label{thermodynamic_dist_U}\\
S & = & Nk \left(\frac{\partial (T \log {\cal Z}_1)}{\partial T}\right)_{V},\label{thermodynamic_dist_S}\\
